1. Add Images to Your Project
your_app/
├── static/
│   └── your_app/
│       ├── images/
│       │   ├── background.jpg
│       │   └── food.jpg


2. Load Static Files in Template
{% load static %}


3. Style the Homepage with Images
{% extends 'base.html' %}
{% load static %}
{% block title %}Welcome - My Restaurant{% endblock %}

{% block breadcrumbs %}
    <span style="color: #999;">Home</span>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div style="
    background-image: url('{% static 'your_app/images/background.jpg' %}');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    padding: 100px 20px;
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
    font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
">
    <h1 style="font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Welcome to Our Restaurant</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 20px;">Delicious food made with love. Order now and enjoy!</p>
    <a href="{% url 'place_order' %}" style="
        margin-top: 30px;
        display: inline-block;
        background-color: #28a745;
        color: white;
        padding: 15px 30px;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-size: 18px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    ">Order Now</a>
</div>

<!-- Food gallery section -->
<div style="padding: 40px 20px; text-align: center;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 20px;">Our Specials</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; gap: 20px;">
        <img src="{% static 'your_app/images/food.jpg' %}" alt="Delicious Dish" style="width: 300px; height: auto; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);">
        <!-- Repeat <img> blocks with other images if needed -->
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}


4.Configure settings.py
# settings.py
STATIC_URL = '/static/'

# During development only
STATICFILES_DIRS = [ BASE_DIR / 'static' ]

5. Make Sure Static Files Are Served (During Development)
from django.conf import settings
from django.conf.urls.static import static

urlpatterns += static(settings.STATIC_URL, document_root=settings.STATIC_ROOT)


Result
Hero section with a full-width background image
A clear headline, tagline, and call-to-action
A responsive food image gallery
